# Active Directory Home Lab

## Overview

This project documents my hands-on practice with Windows Server 2016 and Active Directory in a virtual lab environment using VirtualBox, together with guided exercises from TryHackMe.

## Objectives

The goal of this lab was to develop practical system administration skills commonly required in IT support roles, including user management, password administration, and Active Directory configuration.

## Environment

- Windows Server 2016
- Windows 10 virtual machine
- Oracle VirtualBox
- NAT networking
- Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)
- TryHackMe learning platform

## Tasks Completed

- Installed Windows Server 2016 in VirtualBox
- Configured a NAT network for virtual machines
- Installed Active Directory Domain Services
- Created Organizational Units (OUs)
- Created and managed user accounts
- Reset user passwords
- Delegated administrative control
- Managed and removed groups
- Explored Group Policy concepts
- Learned about domains, trees, trusts, and forests

## Challenges Encountered

I attempted to join a Windows 10 client to the Active Directory domain but encountered configuration issues. Although I did not complete the domain join successfully, I used the experience to deepen my understanding of Active Directory networking and troubleshooting.

## Skills Demonstrated

- Windows Server administration
- Active Directory user management
- Organizational Unit design
- Password administration
- Group management
- Basic system administration
- IT troubleshooting
- Virtualization with VirtualBox

